constructors.name: localFile

args.description: Local path to the locally available file part; may be empty

args.description: True, if it is possible to download or generate the file

args.description: True, if the file can be deleted

args.description: True, if the file is currently being downloaded (or a local copy is being generated by some other means)

args.description: True, if the local copy is fully available

args.name: download_offset
args.description: Download will be started from this offset. downloaded_prefix_size is calculated from this offset

args.name: downloaded_prefix_size
args.description: If is_downloading_completed is false, then only some prefix of the file starting from download_offset is ready to be read. downloaded_prefix_size is the size of that prefix in bytes

args.description: Total downloaded file size, in bytes. Can be used only for calculating download progress. The actual file size may be bigger, and some parts of it may contain garbage

constructors.name: remoteFile
constructors.description: Represents a remote file

args.name: id
args.description: Remote file identifier; may be empty. Can be used by the current user across application restarts or even from other devices. Uniquely identifies a file, but a file can have a lot of different valid identifiers. If the identifier starts with "http://" or "https://", it represents the HTTP URL of the file. TDLib is currently unable to download files if only their URL is known. If downloadFile/addFileToDownloads is called on such a file or if it is sent to a secret chat, TDLib starts a file generation process by sending updateFileGenerationStart to the application with the HTTP URL in the original_path and "#url#" as the conversion string. Application must generate the file by downloading it to the specified location

args.name: unique_id
args.description: Unique file identifier; may be empty if unknown. The unique file identifier which is the same for the same file even for different users and is persistent over time

args.name: is_uploading_active
args.description: True, if the file is currently being uploaded (or a remote copy is being generated by some other means)

args.name: is_uploading_completed
args.description: True, if a remote copy is fully available

args.name: uploaded_size
args.description: Size of the remote available part of the file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

For example, if the file is from a message, then the message must be not deleted and accessible to the user. If the file database is disabled, then the corresponding object with the file must be preloaded by the application

args.description: Local path to a file from which the file is generated. The path doesn't have to be a valid path and is used by TDLib only to detect name and MIME type of the generated file

From the point of view of the system, a channel is a special kind of a supergroup: only administrators can post and see the list of members, and posts from all administrators use the name and photo of the channel instead of individual names and profile photos. Unlike supergroups, channels can have an unlimited number of subscribers

args.name: key_hash
args.description: Hash of the currently used key for comparison with the hash of the chat partner's key. This is a string of 36 little-endian bytes, which must be split into groups of 2 bits, each denoting a pixel of one of 4 colors FFFFFF, D5E6F3, 2D5775, and 2F99C9. The pixels must be used to make a 12x12 square image filled from left to right, top to bottom. Alternatively, the first 32 bytes of the hash can be converted to the hexadecimal format and printed as 32 2-digit hex numbers

args.name: layer
args.description: Secret chat layer; determines features supported by the chat partner's application. Nested text entities and underline and strikethrough entities are supported if the layer >= 101, files bigger than 2000MB are supported if the layer >= 143, spoiler and custom emoji text entities are supported if the layer >= 144

constructors.name: internalLinkTypeAttachmentMenuBot
constructors.description: The link is a link to an attachment menu bot to be opened in the specified or a chosen chat. Process given target_chat to open the chat. Then, call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot and can be added to attachment menu. Then, use getAttachmentMenuBot to receive information about the bot. If the bot isn't added to attachment menu, then show a disclaimer about Mini Apps being third-party applications, ask the user to accept their Terms of service and confirm adding the bot to side and attachment menu. If the user accept the terms and confirms adding, then use toggleBotIsAddedToAttachmentMenu to add the bot. If the attachment menu bot can't be used in the opened chat, show an error to the user. If the bot is added to attachment menu and can be used in the chat, then use openWebApp with the given URL

args.name: target_chat
args.description: Target chat to be opened

args.name: bot_username
args.description: Username of the bot

args.name: url
args.description: URL to be passed to openWebApp

constructors.name: internalLinkTypeBotAddToChannel
constructors.description: The link is a link to a Telegram bot, which is expected to be added to a channel chat as an administrator. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username and check that the user is a bot, ask the current user to select a channel chat to add the bot to as an administrator. Then, call getChatMember to receive the current bot rights in the chat and if the bot already is an administrator, check that the current user can edit its administrator rights and combine received rights with the requested administrator rights. Then, show confirmation box to the user, and call setChatMemberStatus with the chosen chat and confirmed rights

args.name: bot_username
args.description: Username of the bot

args.name: administrator_rights
args.description: Expected administrator rights for the bot

constructors.name: internalLinkTypeBotStart
constructors.description: The link is a link to a chat with a Telegram bot. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot, show START button in the chat with the bot, and then call sendBotStartMessage with the given start parameter after the button is pressed

args.name: bot_username
args.description: Username of the bot

args.name: start_parameter
args.description: The parameter to be passed to sendBotStartMessage

args.name: autostart
args.description: True, if sendBotStartMessage must be called automatically without showing the START button

constructors.name: internalLinkTypeBotStartInGroup
constructors.description: The link is a link to a Telegram bot, which is expected to be added to a group chat. Call searchPublicChat with the given bot username, check that the user is a bot and can be added to groups, ask the current user to select a basic group or a supergroup chat to add the bot to, taking into account that bots can be added to a public supergroup only by administrators of the supergroup. If administrator rights are provided by the link, call getChatMember to receive the current bot rights in the chat and if the bot already is an administrator, check that the current user can edit its administrator rights, combine received rights with the requested administrator rights, show confirmation box to the user, and call setChatMemberStatus with the chosen chat and confirmed administrator rights. Before call to setChatMemberStatus it may be required to upgrade the chosen basic group chat to a supergroup chat. Then, if start_parameter isn't empty, call sendBotStartMessage with the given start parameter and the chosen chat; otherwise, just send /start message with bot's username added to the chat

args.name: bot_username
args.description: Username of the bot

args.name: start_parameter
args.description: The parameter to be passed to sendBotStartMessage

args.name: administrator_rights
args.description: Expected administrator rights for the bot; may be null

types.name: BlockList

functions.name: getAuthorizationState
functions.description: Returns the current authorization state. This is an offline method. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: setTdlibParameters
functions.description: Sets the parameters for TDLib initialization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitTdlibParameters

args.name: use_test_dc
args.description: Pass true to use Telegram test environment instead of the production environment

args.name: database_directory
args.description: The path to the directory for the persistent database; if empty, the current working directory will be used

args.name: files_directory
args.description: The path to the directory for storing files; if empty, database_directory will be used

args.name: database_encryption_key
args.description: Encryption key for the database. If the encryption key is invalid, then an error with code 401 will be returned

args.name: use_file_database
args.description: Pass true to keep information about downloaded and uploaded files between application restarts

args.name: use_chat_info_database
args.description: Pass true to keep cache of users, basic groups, supergroups, channels and secret chats between restarts. Implies use_file_database

args.name: use_message_database
args.description: Pass true to keep cache of chats and messages between restarts. Implies use_chat_info_database

args.name: use_secret_chats
args.description: Pass true to enable support for secret chats

args.name: api_id
args.description: Application identifier for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

args.name: api_hash
args.description: Application identifier hash for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

args.name: system_language_code
args.description: IETF language tag of the user's operating system language; must be non-empty

args.name: device_model
args.description: Model of the device the application is being run on; must be non-empty

args.name: system_version
args.description: Version of the operating system the application is being run on. If empty, the version is automatically detected by TDLib

args.name: application_version
args.description: Application version; must be non-empty

functions.name: setAuthenticationPhoneNumber
functions.description: Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress, authorizationStateWaitEmailCode, authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword

args.name: phone_number
args.description: The phone number of the user, in international format

args.name: settings
args.description: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number; pass null to use default settings

functions.name: setAuthenticationEmailAddress
functions.description: Sets the email address of the user and sends an authentication code to the email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress

args.name: email_address
args.description: The email address of the user

functions.name: resendAuthenticationCode
functions.description: Resends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode, the next_code_type of the result is not null and the server-specified timeout has passed, or when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode

args.name: reason
args.description: Reason of code resending; pass null if unknown

functions.name: checkAuthenticationEmailCode
functions.description: Checks the authentication of an email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode

args.name: code
args.description: Email address authentication to check

functions.name: checkAuthenticationCode
functions.description: Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

args.name: code
args.description: Authentication code to check

functions.name: requestQrCodeAuthentication
functions.description: Requests QR code authentication by scanning a QR code on another logged in device. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress, authorizationStateWaitEmailCode, authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword

args.name: other_user_ids
args.description: List of user identifiers of other users currently using the application

functions.name: registerUser
functions.description: Finishes user registration. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitRegistration

args.name: first_name
args.description: The first name of the user; 1-64 characters

args.name: last_name
args.description: The last name of the user; 0-64 characters

args.name: disable_notification
args.description: Pass true to disable notification about the current user joining Telegram for other users that added them to contact list

functions.name: resetAuthenticationEmailAddress
functions.description: Resets the login email address. May return an error with a message "TASK_ALREADY_EXISTS" if reset is still pending. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode and authorization_state.can_reset_email_address == true

functions.name: checkAuthenticationPassword
functions.description: Checks the 2-step verification password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

args.name: password
args.description: The 2-step verification password to check

functions.name: requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery
functions.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

functions.name: checkAuthenticationPasswordRecoveryCode
functions.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

args.name: recovery_code
args.description: Recovery code to check

functions.name: recoverAuthenticationPassword
functions.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

args.name: recovery_code
args.description: Recovery code to check

args.name: new_password
args.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

args.name: new_hint
args.description: New password hint; may be empty

functions.name: sendAuthenticationFirebaseSms
functions.description: Sends Firebase Authentication SMS to the phone number of the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the server returned code of the type authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseAndroid or authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseIos

args.name: token
args.description: Play Integrity API or SafetyNet Attestation API token for the Android application, or secret from push notification for the iOS application

functions.name: reportAuthenticationCodeMissing
functions.description: Reports that authentication code wasn't delivered via SMS; for official mobile applications only. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

args.name: mobile_network_code
args.description: Current mobile network code

functions.name: checkAuthenticationBotToken
functions.description: Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in

args.name: token
args.description: The bot token

functions.name: logOut
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

functions.name: close
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: destroy
functions.description: Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before authorization

functions.name: confirmQrCodeAuthentication
functions.description: Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success

args.name: link
args.description: A link from a QR code. The link must be scanned by the in-app camera

functions.name: getCurrentState
functions.description: Returns all updates needed to restore current TDLib state, i.e. all actual updateAuthorizationState/updateUser/updateNewChat and others. This is especially useful if TDLib is run in a separate process. Can be called before initialization

functions.name: setDatabaseEncryptionKey
functions.description: Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain

args.name: new_encryption_key
args.description: New encryption key

functions.name: getPasswordState
functions.description: Returns the current state of 2-step verification

functions.name: setPassword
functions.description: Changes the 2-step verification password for the current user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed

args.name: old_password
args.description: Previous 2-step verification password of the user

args.name: new_password
args.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

args.name: new_hint
args.description: New password hint; may be empty

args.name: set_recovery_email_address
args.description: Pass true to change also the recovery email address

args.name: new_recovery_email_address
args.description: New recovery email address; may be empty

functions.name: setLoginEmailAddress
functions.description: Changes the login email address of the user. The email address can be changed only if the current user already has login email and passwordState.login_email_address_pattern is non-empty. The change will not be applied until the new login email address is confirmed with checkLoginEmailAddressCode. To use Apple ID/Google ID instead of an email address, call checkLoginEmailAddressCode directly

args.name: new_login_email_address
args.description: New login email address

functions.name: resendLoginEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Resends the login email address verification code

functions.name: checkLoginEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Checks the login email address authentication

args.name: code
args.description: Email address authentication to check

functions.name: getRecoveryEmailAddress
functions.description: Returns a 2-step verification recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user

args.name: password
args.description: The 2-step verification password for the current user

functions.name: setRecoveryEmailAddress
functions.description: Changes the 2-step verification recovery email address of the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed. If new_recovery_email_address is the same as the email address that is currently set up, this call succeeds immediately and aborts all other requests waiting for an email confirmation

args.name: password
args.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

args.name: new_recovery_email_address
args.description: New recovery email address

functions.name: checkRecoveryEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

args.name: code
args.description: Verification code to check

functions.name: resendRecoveryEmailAddressCode
functions.description: Resends the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

functions.name: cancelRecoveryEmailAddressVerification
functions.description: Cancels verification of the 2-step verification recovery email address

functions.name: requestPasswordRecovery
functions.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up

functions.name: checkPasswordRecoveryCode
functions.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid

args.name: recovery_code
args.description: Recovery code to check

functions.name: recoverPassword
functions.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up

args.name: recovery_code
args.description: Recovery code to check

args.name: new_password
args.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

args.name: new_hint
args.description: New password hint; may be empty

functions.name: resetPassword
functions.description: Removes 2-step verification password without previous password and access to recovery email address. The password can't be reset immediately and the request needs to be repeated after the specified time

functions.name: cancelPasswordReset
functions.description: Cancels reset of 2-step verification password. The method can be called if passwordState.pending_reset_date > 0

functions.name: createTemporaryPassword
functions.description: Creates a new temporary password for processing payments

args.name: password
args.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

args.name: valid_for
args.description: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; must be between 60 and 86400

functions.name: getTemporaryPasswordState
functions.description: Returns information about the current temporary password

functions.name: getMe
functions.description: Returns the current user

functions.name: getUser
functions.description: Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot

args.name: user_id
args.description: User identifier

functions.name: getUserFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a user by their identifier

args.name: user_id
args.description: User identifier

functions.name: getBasicGroup
functions.description: Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot

args.name: basic_group_id
args.description: Basic group identifier

functions.name: getBasicGroupFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier

args.name: basic_group_id
args.description: Basic group identifier

functions.name: getSupergroup
functions.description: Returns information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot

args.name: supergroup_id
args.description: Supergroup or channel identifier

functions.name: getSupergroupFullInfo
functions.description: Returns full information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute

args.name: supergroup_id
args.description: Supergroup or channel identifier

functions.name: getSecretChat
functions.description: Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline method

args.name: secret_chat_id
args.description: Secret chat identifier

functions.name: getChat
functions.description: Returns information about a chat by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

functions.name: getMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a message. Returns a 404 error if the message doesn't exist

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message to get

functions.name: getMessageLocally
functions.description: Returns information about a message, if it is available without sending network request. Returns a 404 error if message isn't available locally. This is an offline method

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message to get

functions.name: getRepliedMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a non-bundled message that is replied by a given message. Also, returns the pinned message, the game message, the invoice message, the message with a previously set same background, the giveaway message, and the topic creation message for messages of the types messagePinMessage, messageGameScore, messagePaymentSuccessful, messageChatSetBackground, messageGiveawayCompleted and topic messages without non-bundled replied message respectively. Returns a 404 error if the message doesn't exist

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the reply message

functions.name: getChatPinnedMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a newest pinned message in the chat. Returns a 404 error if the message doesn't exist

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

functions.name: getCallbackQueryMessage
functions.description: Returns information about a message with the callback button that originated a callback query; for bots only

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

args.name: message_id
args.description: Message identifier

args.name: callback_query_id
args.description: Identifier of the callback query

functions.name: getMessages
functions.description: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat the messages belong to

args.name: message_ids
args.description: Identifiers of the messages to get

functions.name: getMessageProperties
functions.description: Returns properties of a message. This is an offline method

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getMessageThread
functions.description: Returns information about a message thread. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_message_thread == true

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getMessageReadDate
functions.description: Returns read date of a recent outgoing message in a private chat. The method can be called if messageProperties.can_get_read_date == true

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getMessageViewers
functions.description: Returns viewers of a recent outgoing message in a basic group or a supergroup chat. For video notes and voice notes only users, opened content of the message, are returned. The method can be called if messageProperties.can_get_viewers == true

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message

functions.name: getFile
functions.description: Returns information about a file. This is an offline method

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file to get

functions.name: getRemoteFile
functions.description: Returns information about a file by its remote identifier. This is an offline method. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message. Even the request succeeds, the file can be used only if it is still accessible to the user. For example, if the file is from a message, then the message must be not deleted and accessible to the user. If the file database is disabled, then the corresponding object with the file must be preloaded by the application

args.name: remote_file_id
args.description: Remote identifier of the file to get

args.name: file_type
args.description: File type; pass null if unknown

functions.name: loadChats
functions.description: Loads more chats from a chat list. The loaded chats and their positions in the chat list will be sent through updates. Chats are sorted by the pair (chat.position.order, chat.id) in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all chats have been loaded

args.name: chat_list
args.description: The chat list in which to load chats; pass null to load chats from the main chat list

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded chats is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

functions.name: getChats
functions.description: Returns an ordered list of chats from the beginning of a chat list. For informational purposes only. Use loadChats and updates processing instead to maintain chat lists in a consistent state

args.name: chat_list
args.description: The chat list in which to return chats; pass null to get chats from the main chat list

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: searchPublicChat
functions.description: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise, an error is returned

args.name: username
args.description: Username to be resolved

functions.name: searchPublicChats
functions.description: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Excludes private chats with contacts and chats from the chat list from the results

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

functions.name: searchChats
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats. This is an offline method. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for. If the query is empty, returns up to 50 recently found chats

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: searchChatsOnServer
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: getRecommendedChats
functions.description: Returns a list of channel chats recommended to the current user

functions.name: getChatSimilarChats
functions.description: Returns a list of chats similar to the given chat

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

functions.name: getChatSimilarChatCount
functions.description: Returns approximate number of chats similar to the given chat

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

args.name: return_local
args.description: Pass true to get the number of chats without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of chats is unknown locally

functions.name: openChatSimilarChat
functions.description: Informs TDLib that a chat was opened from the list of similar chats. The method is independent of openChat and closeChat methods

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the original chat, which similar chats were requested

args.name: opened_chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the opened chat

functions.name: getBotSimilarBots
functions.description: Returns a list of bots similar to the given bot

args.name: bot_user_id
args.description: User identifier of the target bot

functions.name: getBotSimilarBotCount
functions.description: Returns approximate number of bots similar to the given bot

args.name: bot_user_id
args.description: User identifier of the target bot

args.name: return_local
args.description: Pass true to get the number of bots without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of bots is unknown locally

functions.name: openBotSimilarBot
functions.description: Informs TDLib that a bot was opened from the list of similar bots

args.name: bot_user_id
args.description: Identifier of the original bot, which similar bots were requested

args.name: opened_bot_user_id
args.description: Identifier of the opened bot

functions.name: getTopChats
functions.description: Returns a list of frequently used chats

args.name: category
args.description: Category of chats to be returned

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 30

functions.name: removeTopChat
functions.description: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

args.name: category
args.description: Category of frequently used chats

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

functions.name: searchRecentlyFoundChats
functions.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of up to 50 recently found chats. This is an offline method

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: addRecentlyFoundChat
functions.description: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat to add

functions.name: removeRecentlyFoundChat
functions.description: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat to be removed

functions.name: clearRecentlyFoundChats
functions.description: Clears the list of recently found chats

functions.name: getRecentlyOpenedChats
functions.description: Returns recently opened chats. This is an offline method. Returns chats in the order of last opening

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

functions.name: checkChatUsername
functions.description: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier; must be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or 0 if the chat is being created

args.name: username
args.description: Username to be checked

functions.name: getCreatedPublicChats
functions.description: Returns a list of public chats of the specified type, owned by the user

args.name: type
args.description: Type of the public chats to return

functions.name: checkCreatedPublicChatsLimit
functions.description: Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

args.name: type
args.description: Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit

functions.name: getSuitableDiscussionChats
functions.description: Returns a list of basic group and supergroup chats, which can be used as a discussion group for a channel. Returned basic group chats must be first upgraded to supergroups before they can be set as a discussion group. To set a returned supergroup as a discussion group, access to its old messages must be enabled using toggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable first

functions.name: getInactiveSupergroupChats
functions.description: Returns a list of recently inactive supergroups and channels. Can be used when user reaches limit on the number of joined supergroups and channels and receives CHANNELS_TOO_MUCH error. Also, the limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

functions.name: getSuitablePersonalChats
functions.description: Returns a list of channel chats, which can be used as a personal chat

functions.name: loadSavedMessagesTopics
functions.description: Loads more Saved Messages topics. The loaded topics will be sent through updateSavedMessagesTopic. Topics are sorted by their topic.order in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all topics have been loaded

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of topics to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded topics is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

functions.name: getSavedMessagesTopicHistory
functions.description: Returns messages in a Saved Messages topic. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be fetched

args.name: from_message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

args.name: offset
args.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

functions.name: getSavedMessagesTopicMessageByDate
functions.description: Returns the last message sent in a Saved Messages topic no later than the specified date

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which message will be returned

args.name: date
args.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

functions.name: deleteSavedMessagesTopicHistory
functions.description: Deletes all messages in a Saved Messages topic

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be deleted

functions.name: deleteSavedMessagesTopicMessagesByDate
functions.description: Deletes all messages between the specified dates in a Saved Messages topic. Messages sent in the last 30 seconds will not be deleted

args.name: min_date

args.name: max_date

functions.name: toggleSavedMessagesTopicIsPinned
functions.description: Changes the pinned state of a Saved Messages topic. There can be up to getOption("pinned_saved_messages_topic_count_max") pinned topics. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic to pin or unpin

args.name: is_pinned
args.description: Pass true to pin the topic; pass false to unpin it

functions.name: setPinnedSavedMessagesTopics
functions.description: Changes the order of pinned Saved Messages topics

args.name: saved_messages_topic_ids
args.description: Identifiers of the new pinned Saved Messages topics

functions.name: getGroupsInCommon
functions.description: Returns a list of common group chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

args.name: user_id
args.description: User identifier

args.name: offset_chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier starting from which to return chats; use 0 for the first request

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 100

functions.name: getChatHistory
functions.description: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib. This is an offline method if only_local is true

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: from_message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

args.name: offset
args.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: only_local
args.description: Pass true to get only messages that are available without sending network requests

functions.name: getMessageThreadHistory
functions.description: Returns messages in a message thread of a message. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_message_thread == true. Message thread of a channel message is in the channel's linked supergroup. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: message_id
args.description: Message identifier, which thread history needs to be returned

args.name: from_message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

args.name: offset
args.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

functions.name: deleteChatHistory
functions.description: Deletes all messages in the chat. Use chat.can_be_deleted_only_for_self and chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users fields to find whether and how the method can be applied to the chat

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

args.name: remove_from_chat_list
args.description: Pass true to remove the chat from all chat lists

args.name: revoke
args.description: Pass true to delete chat history for all users

functions.name: deleteChat
functions.description: Deletes a chat along with all messages in the corresponding chat for all chat members. For group chats this will release the usernames and remove all members. Use the field chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users to find whether the method can be applied to the chat

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier

functions.name: searchChatMessages
functions.description: Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query (searchSecretMessages must be used instead), or without an enabled message database. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit. A combination of query, sender_id, filter and message_thread_id search criteria is expected to be supported, only if it is required for Telegram official application implementation

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat in which to search messages

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

args.name: sender_id
args.description: Identifier of the sender of messages to search for; pass null to search for messages from any sender. Not supported in secret chats

args.name: from_message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

args.name: offset
args.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset to get the specified message and some newer messages

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: filter
args.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages

args.name: message_thread_id
args.description: If not 0, only messages in the specified thread will be returned; supergroups only

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: If not 0, only messages in the specified Saved Messages topic will be returned; pass 0 to return all messages, or for chats other than Saved Messages

functions.name: searchMessages
functions.description: Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)). For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: chat_list
args.description: Chat list in which to search messages; pass null to search in all chats regardless of their chat list. Only Main and Archive chat lists are supported

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

args.name: offset
args.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: filter
args.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages. Filters searchMessagesFilterMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadReaction, searchMessagesFilterFailedToSend, and searchMessagesFilterPinned are unsupported in this function

args.name: chat_type_filter
args.description: Additional filter for type of the chat of the searched messages; pass null to search for messages in all chats

args.name: min_date
args.description: If not 0, the minimum date of the messages to return

args.name: max_date
args.description: If not 0, the maximum date of the messages to return

functions.name: searchSecretMessages
functions.description: Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat in which to search. Specify 0 to search in all secret chats

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for. If empty, searchChatMessages must be used instead

args.name: offset
args.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: filter
args.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages

functions.name: searchSavedMessages
functions.description: Searches for messages tagged by the given reaction and with the given words in the Saved Messages chat; for Telegram Premium users only. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

args.name: saved_messages_topic_id
args.description: If not 0, only messages in the specified Saved Messages topic will be considered; pass 0 to consider all messages

args.name: tag
args.description: Tag to search for; pass null to return all suitable messages

args.name: query
args.description: Query to search for

args.name: from_message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

args.name: offset
args.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative offset to get the specified message and some newer messages

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than -offset. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

functions.name: searchCallMessages

args.description: Identifier of the chat from which to forward messages

args.name: message_ids
args.description: Identifiers of the messages to forward. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order. At most 100 messages can be forwarded simultaneously. A message can be forwarded only if messageProperties.can_be_forwarded

args.name: options
args.description: Options to be used to send the messages; pass null to use default options

args.name: send_copy
args.description: Pass true to copy content of the messages without reference to the original sender. Always true if the messages are forwarded to a secret chat or are local. Use messageProperties.can_be_saved and messageProperties.can_be_copied_to_secret_chat to check whether the message is suitable

args.name: remove_caption
args.description: Pass true to remove media captions of message copies. Ignored if send_copy is false

functions.name: sendQuickReplyShortcutMessages
functions.description: Sends messages from a quick reply shortcut. Requires Telegram Business subscription. Can't be used to send paid messages

args.description: Identifier of the chat to which to send messages. The chat must be a private chat with a regular user

args.name: shortcut_id
args.description: Unique identifier of the quick reply shortcut

args.name: sending_id
args.description: Non-persistent identifier, which will be returned back in messageSendingStatePending object and can be used to match sent messages and corresponding updateNewMessage updates

functions.name: resendMessages
functions.description: Resends messages which failed to send. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed. If a message is re-sent, the corresponding failed to send message is deleted. Returns the sent messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be re-sent, null will be returned instead of the message

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat to send messages

args.name: message_ids
args.description: Identifiers of the messages to resend. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order

args.name: quote
args.description: New manually chosen quote from the message to be replied; pass null if none. Ignored if more than one message is re-sent, or if messageSendingStateFailed.need_another_reply_quote == false

args.name: paid_message_star_count
args.description: The number of Telegram Stars the user agreed to pay to send the messages. Ignored if messageSendingStateFailed.required_paid_message_star_count == 0

functions.name: addLocalMessage

args.name: reply_to

functions.name: shareChatWithBot
functions.description: Shares a chat after pressing a keyboardButtonTypeRequestChat button with the bot

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Identifier of the chat with the bot

args.name: message_id
args.description: Identifier of the message with the button

args.name: button_id
args.description: Identifier of the button

args.description: Identifier of the shared chat

args.name: only_check
args.description: Pass true to check that the chat can be shared by the button instead of actually sharing it. Doesn't check bot_is_member and bot_administrator_rights restrictions. If the bot must be a member, then all chats from getGroupsInCommon and all chats, where the user can add the bot, are suitable. In the latter case the bot will be automatically added to the chat. If the bot must be an administrator, then all chats, where the bot already has requested rights or can be added to administrators by the user, are suitable. In the latter case the bot will be automatically granted requested rights

functions.name: downloadFile
functions.description: Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file to download

args.name: priority
args.description: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first

args.name: offset
args.description: The starting position from which the file needs to be downloaded

args.name: limit
args.description: Number of bytes which need to be downloaded starting from the "offset" position before the download will automatically be canceled; use 0 to download without a limit

args.name: synchronous
args.description: Pass true to return response only after the file download has succeeded, has failed, has been canceled, or a new downloadFile request with different offset/limit parameters was sent; pass false to return file state immediately, just after the download has been started

functions.name: getFileDownloadedPrefixSize
functions.description: Returns file downloaded prefix size from a given offset, in bytes

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file

args.name: offset
args.description: Offset from which downloaded prefix size needs to be calculated

functions.name: cancelDownloadFile
functions.description: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of a file to stop downloading

args.name: only_if_pending
args.description: Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn't been started, i.e. request hasn't been sent to server

functions.name: getSuggestedFileName
functions.description: Returns suggested name for saving a file in a given directory

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file

args.name: directory
args.description: Directory in which the file is expected to be saved

functions.name: preliminaryUploadFile
functions.description: Preliminary uploads a file to the cloud before sending it in a message, which can be useful for uploading of being recorded voice and video notes. In all other cases there is no need to preliminary upload a file. Updates updateFile will be used to notify about upload progress. The upload will not be completed until the file is sent in a message

args.name: file
args.description: File to upload

args.name: file_type
args.description: File type; pass null if unknown

args.name: priority
args.description: Priority of the upload (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be uploaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the first one for which preliminaryUploadFile was called will be uploaded first

functions.name: cancelPreliminaryUploadFile
functions.description: Stops the preliminary uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using preliminaryUploadFile

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file to stop uploading

functions.name: writeGeneratedFilePart
functions.description: Writes a part of a generated file. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct write to the destination file

args.name: generation_id
args.description: The identifier of the generation process

args.name: offset
args.description: The offset from which to write the data to the file

args.name: data
args.description: The data to write

functions.name: setFileGenerationProgress
functions.description: Informs TDLib on a file generation progress

args.name: generation_id
args.description: The identifier of the generation process

args.name: expected_size
args.description: Expected size of the generated file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

args.name: local_prefix_size
args.description: The number of bytes already generated

functions.name: finishFileGeneration
functions.description: Finishes the file generation

args.name: generation_id
args.description: The identifier of the generation process

args.name: error
args.description: If passed, the file generation has failed and must be terminated; pass null if the file generation succeeded

functions.name: readFilePart
functions.description: Reads a part of a file from the TDLib file cache and returns read bytes. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct read from the file

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file. The file must be located in the TDLib file cache

args.name: offset
args.description: The offset from which to read the file

args.name: count
args.description: Number of bytes to read. An error will be returned if there are not enough bytes available in the file from the specified position. Pass 0 to read all available data from the specified position

functions.name: deleteFile
functions.description: Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file to delete

functions.name: addFileToDownloads
functions.description: Adds a file from a message to the list of file downloads. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates. If message database is used, the list of file downloads is persistent across application restarts. The downloading is independent of download using downloadFile, i.e. it continues if downloadFile is canceled or is used to download a part of the file

args.name: file_id
args.description: Identifier of the file to download

args.name: chat_id
args.description: Chat identifier of the message with the file

args.name: message_id
args.description: Message identifier

args.name: priority
args.description: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first
